The paper deals with the analysis of pattern matching algorithms, which is a topic that falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The use of probabilistic models and automata also suggests a connection to the sub-category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Additionally, the paper proposes a new framework for probabilistic analysis, which could be of interest to researchers in the fields of formal languages (cs.FL) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the experimental results involve the size of minimal DAAs, which could be relevant to researchers in the area of machine learning (cs.LG).
